casebody.data:
MISCELLANEOUS DISMISSALS

99-1633. Columbia Gas of Ohio v. Zaino.

Board of Tax Appeals, Nos. 97-K-545, 97-K-546 and 97-K-547. This cause, here on appeal from the Board of Tax Appeals, was considered in the manner prescribed by law. Upon consideration of appellant’s application for dismissal,

IT IS ORDERED by the court that the application for dismissal be, and hereby is, granted.

ACCORDINGLY, IT IS FURTHER ORDERED by the court that this cause be, and hereby is, dismissed.
